  "text": "## Chromium Multi-Process Architecture Key Components\n\n### 1. RenderProcessHostImpl (Browser-side Renderer Process Management)\n**Location:** `content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h` (line 195) and `.cc`\n**Class:** `RenderProcessHostImpl`\n**Description:** The browser-side representation of a renderer process. This class manages the renderer process lifecycle, IPC communication, and resource allocation. It implements multiple interfaces including `RenderProcessHost`, `ChildProcessLauncher::Client`, and `mojom::RendererHost`.\n\n### 2. BrowserMainLoop (Main Browser Process Event Loop)\n**Location:** `content/browser/browser_main_loop.h` (line 106) and `browser_main_loop.cc` (line 483)\n**Class:** `BrowserMainLoop`\n**Description:** The main browser process event loop that orchestrates the initialization and shutdown of all browser threads and subsystems. It manages the UI thread, IO thread, and other critical thread pools that handle browser operations.\n\n### 3. RenderThreadImpl (Renderer Process Main Thread)\n**Location:** `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h` (line 126) and `.cc`\n**Class:** `RenderThreadImpl`\n**Description:** The main thread of a renderer process, where `blink::WebView` instances live. It handles most communication via Mojo IPC messages and routes legacy IPC messages based on routing IDs of `RenderFrameImpl` instances. Implements both `RenderThread` and `mojom::Renderer` interfaces.\n\n### 4. ChildProcessLauncher (Process Spawning)\n**Location:** `content/browser/child_process_launcher.h` (line 212) and `.cc`\n**Class:** `ChildProcessLauncher`\n**Description:** Responsible for spawning child processes (including renderer, GPU, utility, and other process types). It handles asynchronous process creation and provides callbacks for clients to monitor process launch success or failure.\n\n### 5. content.mojom.Renderer (Browser-to-Renderer IPC Interface)\n**Location:** `content/common/renderer.mojom` (line 49)\n**Interface:** `Renderer`\n**Description:** The primordial Channel-associated Mojo interface implemented by the render process for browser-to-renderer control messages. This interface maintains FIFO ordering with respect to legacy IPC messages and includes methods like `CreateAgentSchedulingGroup` for setting up renderer-side agent scheduling groups.\n\n## Process Architecture Summary\n\nThe multi-process model works as follows: `BrowserMainLoop` orchestrates the browser process startup and initializes `RenderProcessHostImpl` instances for each renderer process. Each `RenderProcessHostImpl` uses `ChildProcessLauncher` to spawn a separate renderer process that runs `RenderThreadImpl` on its main thread. These processes communicate bidirectionally using Mojo IPC, with the `Renderer` interface handling browser-to-renderer messages and `RendererHost` interface handling renderer-to-browser messages."
}

